values:
Nice guys really do finish last.
I'd be great if something went my way for once.

Studying at the ERC is fun...
So yeah, I'm hoping shit turns around in the next couple days, or finals week my very well be the death of me.

Anyway, want to get together over break?  My parents are gonna be gone for a least a couple nights.  So, party.  That means I need to find someone who can get some beer due to my lack of connections at home.



I deleted a bunch of songs off iTunes for various reasons of not wanting to listen to them.
If anyone has any ideas on songs I may like, send me a message or whatever.
I was just being naive and stupid.  Surprise...
FUCK FUCK FUCK FUCK FUCK FUCK FUCK FUCK FUCK

That was the hardest thing I've ever done in my life, but I had to do it.  Maybe I did it wrong, but it's over now.  It should have never come to that, but I didn't have any control over it...

Now I'm off to be heartbroken...







Had I punched that door any harder, that big crack would be a hole...
I'll be home tomorrow (Monday).  Call me to hang out, or don't, I don't care.
It just hasn't been my week...

I'm gonna be home on Monday night, so that means I have all day Tuesday to do shit too.  Start making plans with me now, because if I have plans, I won't change them.  I really want to go to a party with people I remember, if anyone that reads this... all 2 of you... knows of one that's going on, give me a call or something.


I had something else I was going to say... but I won't go there...

I have no fucking control over anything.  I fucked up being a boyfriend, I fucked up being a friend, I'm fucking up classes, I'm on a fucking roll aren't I?  Why should I try to figure out the future?  I can't even figure out what the fuck I'm doing now.

All I want is to feel like I have control over something.  Everything that's happened lately has had nothing to do with how I've wanted and tried to make it happen.  All I do now is worry about stuff.  It's taking it's toll on me, and it needs to stop.

Now it seems I can't keep my mind of you My brain drifts back to better days we've been through Like sitting on blacktop of the school grounds The love I bitched about I finally found But now it's gone and I take the blame So there's nothing I can do but take the pain Why? Now I dwell on what you remind me of A sweet young girl who sacrificed her love As for me... I am blind without a cause And now I realize what I have lost It was something real that I could have had Now I play the fool whose stable soul's gone bad Why? Tell me the words I might have said That's pumping pressure deep inside my head Was it bad enough to be too late? Just tell me the words I might have ate But now it's gone and I take the blame So there's nothing I can do but take the pain Why?

Right now, I feel the same way I did on March 27th, 2004, only about a million times worse.
I'm definately beyond depressed right now.  I ruin everything good that comes into my life.  I suggest that anyone who doesn't want to get their life fucked up by me, and be sad because of me, just avoid me now, because it'll happen.

I think I'm just going to lay in bed for the rest of my life and hope I die.
I decided that there's no point in having another journal, I can just say what I want here.  I don't care.

Scratch that, that other journal is going to be the one where I get shit out and not care.  If you want to read it, well, let's just say the odds of anyone being allowed to read it are slim to none, and slim can fuck off and die.
I created a new LJ.  If you want it, ask, if not, I don't care.

Taking chances isn't for me.  I'm only going with sure things from now on.

Not knowing that you were wrong for 3 days isn't exactly a great feeling.  Oh well, I just fell for a joke.  Joke's on me.




My computer is totally fucked up.  If you happen to be talking to me online, and I just suddenly leave, my computer did it.

I'm starting to think I need a haircut.  I mean, I found out last night that my hair is almost as long as Hilary's. :-P  Well, my hair is cool, and even though I think I need a haircut, I'm at least going to keep growing it out until I get home, at which point I'll let everyone I know that sees me criticize me.  Fuckers, it's MY hair!

Man, if I was totally stupid all the time, I'd have a lot of problems.

It's a good thing I'm only totally stupid some of the time.

Eh, what can you do?
Nyquil, well, the generic brand I happen to have up at school fucking rocks.  The pills may be huge, but they're so worth it if you feel like shit.

I need Red Forman around to call me a dumbass when I do something stupid.

For those of you that don't know, and should also be shot, Red Forman is the father from That 70's Show.
So as far as I can tell, everything that could've gone wrong today, did.  Fantastic.  Oh well.  Tomorrow's another day.

I'd probably give anything just so I could have a clear head and fall right asleep some night.  This not sleeping garbage is starting to fuck me up bad, as I need to take a nap pretty much everyday just to feel like I can function.  Somebody, anybody, help me sleep somehow.

My birthday rocked.  I drank beer all day.  Played video games.  Rocked out.  Talked to my mom and my grandma while plastered, that was entertaining to say the least.  I even got a phone call from Robert Masterson himself.  It was fucking awesome.  Thanks everyone, it was a really good day.

Today is recovery day.  Blah.
I'm so drunk... but Happy Birthday to me!

Holy shit, my birthday's tomorrow.
Thirsty Thursday + Birthday Celebration = ... What time do I wake up tomorrow again?...

One half of me feels like it's pretty much taking a shit on the other half.

In other news, I guess I'm failing the class I thought would be my easiest.  Ironic.
It's why they make music with pianos, accoustic guitars, and string instruments.

I had an epiphany (However the fuck that's spelled.  Well, I'm drunk, I don't care how it's spelled.)  Anyway, I was sitting in the newly dubbed "Shiigg", and it was dark, and I had a few beers in me.  Jim started talking about his coming down from his high, and I started to think.  All of the sudden, I hit somewhere I'd never been before.  In a dark room, with Pink Floyd's "Wish You Were Here" playing, I felt something that was in indescribable.  I went from the highest high of happiness in my life to the lowest low that I've ever felt.  I went back and forth, it was like a struggle in my mind.  I went from ready to fucking cry, to smiling uncontrollably half a dozen times, just thinking about everything that's happened in my life.  I wish I would have been able to stay there, it was amazing.  I honestly felt like I was on another fucking planet.  I didn't want to come home.  I want to go back there, it was just unbelieveable.  It also confirmed a lot of shit that I realized in the last couple days.  I don't want to talk about a lot of the things I've come to figure out, but they're all fucking true.  My outlook on how shit works is totally different than how it used to be.  I just wish I could go back to where I was.  It was just, amazing.  I still and jumping back and forth between absolute love and happiness and absolute hatred and depression, and I wasn't even the one doing the drugs.


Wow, just... wow.

Heaven from Hell...

Once again, Cub 1 pussies out, and there's no fucking football game.  That's the only fucking reason I got out of bed this morning.  What a bunch of fucking assholes.  If you're gonna talk shit and say that you're ready to come play, don't fucking decide that you don't want to play.


Fuck you Cub 1, fuck you.
I still do what I'm told, and I don't even have a reason to.  Why?  Why do I do it?

It's not that I want to be someone else,
there's just a lot of things about myself I want to change...
So when is someone gonna come visit me?

So I managed through a divine miracle, an 82 on my Materials Science exam.  I don't know how, but I won't ask any questions as to why.  I had two exams today, I think I did alright on both of them.  Psychology and Differential Equations.  I guess I'm doing pretty well in school, a lot better than I thought I was doing anyway.

My birthday is coming up soon.  That's always cool.

So the highly anticipated 04-05 Rey 2 vs. 05-06 Cub 1 rematch was a bust.  No one from there floor even showed up.  Bunch of pussies.  However, it did turn into the Rey 2 watch Austin toss Dan around like a ragdoll reunion.  The ground was nice and soft from the 2 weeks of non-stop rain.  After that I decided to slide through the mudhole in the middle of the field.  That was probably a mistake, but it was fun.

So I have two exams on Tuesday, Psychology and Differential Equations.  I should probably study more for Psychology than I did for the first one, which was no studying...  Heh.  The Diff Eq exam is the only one before the final, so I kind of need to do well.  I'm doing pretty well in the class, so I'm probably okay.

I got an 87 on my Electrical Science exam, which is great.  Even though apparently you got 50 for showing up because of his retarded grading scheme.  I still haven't gotten my Materials Science exam back, but I don't really want that one back...

That's right Danny, since you're so good at it you might as well keep fucking doing it, it's obivously making everything better you idiot.


You'd think I wanted it to be like this, the way I seem to fuck it up over and over and over and over...
My birthday is coming up...  less than two weeks now...

Well, I broke the streak, I almost had 2 months.  Oh well.  I lasted a lot longer than I thought I would.

I'll try to stop before I go to diff eq, or maybe I won't go, I haven't decided yet...

Should I just like, find a trash can now?

The rest of me needs to tell my head to pull itself out of my ass...
My knee needs to stop hurting for no apparent reason.

Well, this weekend turned out to be really good and really shitty at the same time.

The really good part is that I got to be with Julie for a bit, and that made me feel a lot better.

The really shitty part is that I got fucking rear-ended, and not only are my parents practically disowning me, but... well fuck it, I don't care, I'm just mad I don't get to go to Oswego.



Thanksgiving break isn't that far away.
I'm really happy things are back to normal.

The only one that will understand this is Tom, but I don't care.


I beat the NS on KoL.
My life is complete.
I wish I was perfect.  That way, nothing could ever go wrong.  Everything would be how it's supposed to be.
Is it healthy if your stomach feels like it's eating itself?

You know what, I learned a lot about myself, life, and other shit last night.  I didn't realize it until I woke up.  I came up to Oswego, where I still am, on the account I still need a couple hours before I go driving anywhere, to just not think about anything and just not myself.  In the end, I was more like myself last night than I've been in a long time.  It may have something to do with, as my friends call it, "liquid courage", but I was just myself.  I was shy, but I said all the stupid things that I'd expect myself to say when I was drunk.  I made fun of kids twice my size, I said things to girls that I certainly would never say sober, and I acted like a total fuck up, but I was still me more than... ever.  I met a lot of cool people last night.  I mean, I did start drinking at like 7, and didn't get back until 4, so I had a lot of time, but I had more fun last night than any night I've had at Clarkson.  In the end, I still would have gone with my other option, had it been available, but since it wasn't, I'm glad I came up here.  I left a lot of details out, so if you want to know, just ask, I just wanted to get the emotional garbage out, before I forget it.


And by the way, you can't go wrong buying 56 bottles of Molson for $35 even.


Lois:  "Peter are you drunk?
Peter: "I'm not drunk, I'm just exhausted from drinking all night"

That's me right now.  Haha.
I want to be someone else.
